	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I also bought a front-loading NES in a bundle (refurbished with a new 72-pin, can't push down), the seller gave me some games that she said were "broken". It would never work as much as a tried on the one she gave me, but it worked right away on my top-loader NES. On my old regular NES that I had as a kid there were some games that took forever to get working (Zelda 2 was particularly bad).
<br />
<br />Basically, if you mess with them enough and clean the contacts you will eventually get the game working, but it will never work nearly as well as your top-loader. But definitely cut off the CIC as it's annoyingly picky.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


